This paper is about abstract machines for Prolog and related languages, which are typically studied in the programming languages (cs.PL) and software engineering (cs.SE) sub-categories. The paper also discusses optimizations and program transformations, which are relevant to the logic in computer science (cs.LO) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) sub-categories. Finally, the paper mentions the use of low-level languages in implementation, which is relevant to the architecture (cs.AR) sub-category.
